- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with understanding the dynamics of an environment, which is crucial for agents to achieve long-term autonomy in urban environments. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper presents a method that leverages the expressiveness of kernels from non-parametric modelling to predict a multi-modal distribution over possible future trajectories. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible category as the paper deals with capturing the trajectories of movement in an environment, which could involve visual data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with developing methods to capture the multi-modal and probabilistic nature of motion patterns, which is a common problem in AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper deals with predicting the trajectories of movement in an environment, which is a common problem in control systems.
